HOUSE BILL 1033
C8 6lr1858
CF SB 924
By: Delegate Wolek
Introduced and read first time: February 9, 2026
Assigned to: Economic Matters
A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Department of Social and Economic Mobility – Maryland Chamber of Commerce
3 Grant Program – Established
4 (Business Networks Access Act)
5 FOR the purpose of establishing the Maryland Chamber of Commerce Grant Program in
6 the Department of Social and Economic Mobility to provide grants for membership
7 subsidies for underrepresented individuals and inter–chamber events; specifying
8 certain application requirements for the Program; requiring Program applicants to
9 meet certain eligibility requirements; and generally relating to the Maryland
10 Chamber of Commerce Grant Program in the Department of Social and Economic
11 Mobility.
12 BY adding to
13 Article – State Government
14 Section 9–4109
15 Annotated Code of Maryland
16 (2021 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
17 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
18 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
19 Article – State Government
20 9–4109.
21 (A) (1) IN THIS SECTION THE FOLLOWING WORDS HAVE THE MEANINGS
22 INDICATED.
23 (2) “CHAMBER” MEANS A CHAMBER OF COMMERCE IN THE STATE.
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
[Brackets] indicate matter deleted from exist in g l aw . *hb1033*

2 HOUSE BILL 1033
1 (3) “PROGRAM” MEANS THE MARYLAND CHAMBER OF COMMERCE
2 GRANT PROGRAM.
3 (B) THERE IS A MARYLAND CHAMBER OF COMMERCE GRANT PROGRAM IN
4 THE DEPARTMENT.
5 (C) THE PURPOSE OF THE PROGRAM IS TO PROVIDE GRANTS TO CHAMBERS
6 FOR THE FOLLOWING PURPOSES:
7 (1) MEMBERSHIP SUBSIDIES FOR UNDERREPRESENTED
8 INDIVIDUALS; AND
9 (2) INTER–CHAMBER EVENTS.
10 (D) THE DEPARTMENT SHALL DEVELOP A UNIFIED APPLICATION
11 REQUIRING THE FOLLOWING INFORMATION:
12 (1) GRANT TYPE;
13 (2) CHAMBER PROGRAMMING AND CAPACITY TO SUPPORT GRANT
14 ACTIVITIES;
15 (3) POINT OF CONTACT RESPONSIBLE FOR GRANT ADMINISTRATION;
16 (4) PROJECTED TIMELINE;
17 (5) PROPOSED BUDGET;
18 (6) ADDITIONAL INFORMATION AS SPECIFIED BY THE DEPARTMENT;
19 AND
20 (7) FOR MEMBERSHIP SUBSIDIES, A BRIEF JUSTIFICATION OF WHY A
21 POTENTIAL MEMBER IS UNDERREPRESENTED IN A CHAMBER.
22 (E) THE DEPARTMENT SHALL:
23 (1) REVIEW APPLICATIONS;
24 (2) DETERMINE AWARD AMOUNTS; AND
25 (3) NOTIFY CHAMBERS REGARDING AN AWARD.

HOUSE BILL 1033 3
1 (F) (1) TO BE ELIGIBLE FOR A MEMBERSHIP GRANT, A CHAMBER SHALL
2 DEMONSTRATE:
3 (I) OPPORTUNITIES FOR PROGRAMMING, SERVICES,
4 MENTORING, OR NETWORKING FOR NEWLY ENROLLED MEMBERS; AND
5 (II) ANNUAL FUNDING FOR AT LEAST ONE FULL–TIME PAID
6 POSITION.
7 (2) MEMBERSHIP GRANTS MAY BE USED FOR 1 YEAR OF THE
8 LOWEST–TIER CHAMBER MEMBERSHIP AT NO COST TO UNDERREPRESENTED
9 INDIVIDUALS.
10 (3) THE DEPARTMENT SHALL DISBURSE A MEMBERSHIP GRANT TO A
11 CHAMBER WITHIN 14 DAYS AFTER THE CHAMBER ENROLLS A MEMBER.
12 (4) CHAMBERS THAT RECEIVE MEMBERSHIP GRANTS SHALL SUBMIT
13 AN ANNUAL REPORT TO THE DEPARTMENT WITH THE FOLLOWING INFORMATION:
14 (I) THE NUMBER OF INDIVIDUAL AWARDS; AND
15 (II) PARTICIPANT FEEDBACK ON THE UTILITY OF THE
16 CHAMBER’S PROGRAMMING.
17 (G) (1) TWO OR MORE CHAMBERS MAY APPLY JOINTLY FOR AN
18 INTER–CHAMBER GRANT UNDER THIS SECTION.
19 (2) AN APPLICATION SHALL INCLUDE:
20 (I) A PLAN FOR THE PROPOSED EVENT;
21 (II) EXPECTED ATTENDANCE; AND
22 (III) COST.
23 (3) ELIGIBLE USES OF INTER–CHAMBER GRANTS INCLUDE:
24 (I) VENUE EXPENSES;
25 (II) EVENT PROMOTION;
26 (III) STAFF SUPPORT; AND

4 HOUSE BILL 1033
1 (IV) RELATED COSTS.
2 (4) CHAMBERS RECEIVING INTER–CHAMBER GRANTS SHALL SUBMIT
3 A REPORT TO THE DEPARTMENT AFTER EACH EVENT WITH THE FOLLOWING
4 INFORMATION:
5 (I) ATTENDANCE;
6 (II) EVENT ACTIVITIES; AND
7 (III) RECEIPTS FOR EVENT EXPENDITURES.
8 (H) FOR EACH FISCAL YEAR, THE GOVERNOR SHALL INCLUDE IN THE
9 ANNUAL BUDGET BILL AN APPROPRIATION OF $100,000 TO THE DEPARTMENT FOR
10 THE PROGRAM.
11 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
12 October 1, 2026.

